Abengoa Agrees to Build $171 Million Water Desalination Plant in Ghana

-- B y   B e n   S i l l s
-- 
2011-04-29T06:57:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/abengoa-agrees-to-build-171-million-water-desalination-plant-in-ghana.html
Abengoa SA (ABG) , the Spanish engineering
company that produces enough drinking water for 8 million people
each day, agreed to build a 115 million-euro ($171 million)
desalination plant in  Ghana .  The water-treatment plant, located 15 kilometers from the
capital, Accra, will produce 60,000 liters of fresh water a day,
the company said in an emailed press release. Abengoa will
operate the plant for 25 years.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Sills at 
 bsills@bloomberg.net  